.START 

Borden Inc. acquired Fiap Group, a closely held maker of plastic films and rigid plastic packaging based in Milan, Italy, for more than $25 million. 

Borden, a producer of foods, non-food consumer products and packaging and industrial products, said the addition of Fiap will increase its European sales in these businesses by about 60%.
Borden has film operations in Belgium, France, the Netherlands, Spain and the U.K. Borden makes rigid plastic packaging, such as plastic tubs and containers, in France, the Netherlands and the U.K. 

Fiap has manufacturing and sales operations in Italy, Greece, West Germany, France and the U.S. Borden said Fiap's 1989 sales would be about $90 million, compared with about $150 million for Borden's existing European plastic films and packaging units. 

